<!-- Post Header
================================================== -->        
    <header class="center-all">
      <small class="preheader text-center">August 21, 2013</small>
      <hr class="sep-date"/>
    
      <h1 class="post-title">Art.Com steps up their design game</h1>
      <ul class="post-meta">
        <li><span class="post-meta-byline">Written by <a href="http://sosweetcreative.com/author/liggie" title="Posts by Liggie" rel="author">Liggie</a> and Posted in: <a href="http://sosweetcreative.com/category/discover" title="View all posts in Discover">Discover</a> | <a href="http://sosweetcreative.com/category/love" title="View all posts in Love">Love</a></span></li>
      </ul>
    </header>

<!-- Post Content
================================================== -->        
    <div class="post-content">
      <img alt="blogimg-art-com-main" src="http://sosweetcreative.com/wp-content/uploads/blogimg-art-com-main.jpg" width="800" height="500" />
<p>Last year, we noticed <a href="http://art.com">Art.Com</a> had a brand new bag. Their revamped web presence showed off fresh UI design and engaging features. Rather than simply browse endlessly through the artwork, you can now access <a href="http://www.art.com/me/Karen-Kimmel/">curated collections</a>, <a href="http://www.art.com/community/">social elements</a>Â and <a href="http://www.art.com/~/design-inspiration/">design inspiration</a>. While the website always had a huge collection of traditional art, we were pleasantly surprised to find more alternative and pop culture-related works. We spent some time exploring the site and, of course, came back with a few favorites.</p>
<figure class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://www.art.com/products/p16271439895-sa-i6977408/jane-kim-white-lipped-peccary.htm?sorig=cat&amp;sorigid=0&amp;dimvals=5716449&amp;ui=de7437dd82bf4ae4b82f849c794c0866"><img alt="WhiteLipped" src="http://sosweetcreative.com/wp-content/uploads/wildboards.jpg" width="800" height="600" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">// <a href="http://www.art.com/asp/sp.asp?frameSku=9344683_4986478-1361998&amp;ui=DE7437DD82BF4AE4B82F849C794C0866">White Lipped Peccary</a> by Jane Kim//</figcaption></figure>
<figure class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img alt="scoutcrop" src="http://sosweetcreative.com/wp-content/uploads/scoutcrop.jpg" width="800" height="600" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">//Â <a href="http://www.art.com/products/p13375452552-sa-i6454387/richard-phillips-scout-crop.htm">Scout-Crop</a> by Richard Phillips //</figcaption></figure>
<figure class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img alt="wildroses" src="http://sosweetcreative.com/wp-content/uploads/wildroses.jpg" width="800" height="600" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">//Â <a href="http://www.art.com/asp/sp.asp?frameSku=9344684_4986654-3715618&amp;ui=DE7437DD82BF4AE4B82F849C794C0866">Wild Roses</a> by Jane Kim //</figcaption></figure>
<figure class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img alt="" src="http://sosweetcreative.com/wp-content/uploads/sanfranabstract.jpg" width="777" height="500" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">//Â <a href="http://www.art.com/products/p13585528649-sa-i6460029/hero-design-san-francisco.htm?sorig=cat&amp;sorigid=0&amp;dimvals=207231&amp;ui=de7437dd82bf4ae4b82f849c794c0866">San Francisco</a> by Hero Design // <a href="http://www.art.com/products/p13019970-sa-i2266804/ledent-abstract-0805.htm">Abstract 0805</a> by Ledent //</figcaption></figure>
<p>If you have some downtime and need a jolt of art in your life or home, Art.Com is the ultimate treasure trove. For more of our art favorites check out our growing collection here:Â <a href="http://bit.ly/19vOQqK">http://bit.ly/19vOQqK</a></p>
    </div>

